WEBVTT

00:04.771 --> 00:05.672 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.772 --> 00:06.673 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.773 --> 00:08.275 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:

00:08.375 --> 00:09.910 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the United States:We're bringing back jobs.

00:10.010 --> 00:11.812 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
We're bringing down your taxes.

00:11.912 --> 00:16.149 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President Trump moves to roll
back regulations aimed at preventing a financial

00:16.250 --> 00:20.120 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
crisis and imposes new sanctions on Iran.

00:20.220 --> 00:26.260 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Then, we are on the ground in Mosul, as the
battle to control the key Iraqi city rages

00:26.360 --> 00:27.361 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
on.

00:27.461 --> 00:29.696 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
JANE FERGUSON: The front line is just up here.

00:29.796 --> 00:34.668 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
That's where the River Tigris is, and ISIS
fighters are trying to push the Iraqi army

00:34.768 --> 00:35.669 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
back.

00:35.769 --> 00:37.638 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And it's Friday.

00:37.738 --> 00:43.443 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
Mark Shields and David Brooks tackle a tumultuous
first two weeks of the Trump administration.

00:43.543 --> 00:50.150 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
All that and more on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

00:50.250 --> 00:52.953 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:53.053 --> 01:03.130 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The first two weeks of the
Trump presidency are now behind us, punctuated

01:03.230 --> 01:07.167 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
by a push to begin to deregulate the financial
industry.

01:07.267 --> 01:09.970 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
John Yang reports on this day's events.

01:10.070 --> 01:16.743 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JOHN YANG: At the first meeting of this new
economic advisory council, President Trump

01:16.843 --> 01:18.445 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
used touted his plans for progress.

01:18.545 --> 01:20.447 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the United States:We're bringing back jobs.

01:20.547 --> 01:21.448 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
We're bringing down your taxes.

01:21.548 --> 01:22.983 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
&nbsp;
We're getting rid of your regulations.

01:23.083 --> 01:26.486 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
And I think it's going to be some really very
exciting times ahead.

01:26.586 --> 01:31.458 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JOHN YANG: The group talked banking rules
and tax reform.

01:31.558 --> 01:35.629 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
But some also raised concerns that Mr. Trump's
immigration order would hurt their foreign

01:35.729 --> 01:38.131 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
employees and the economy.

01:38.231 --> 01:41.868 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Blackstone Group CEO Steve Schwarzman is the
council's chairman.

01:41.969 --> 01:44.471 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
He described the discussion on FOX Business
Channel.

01:44.571 --> 01:49.142 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
STEPHEN SCHWARZMAN, CEO, Blackstone Group:
General Kelly, who runs Homeland Security,

01:49.242 --> 01:54.881 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
was there and brought people up to date onthe changes that had been made.

01:54.982 --> 02:00.854 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
And there was obviously concern by different
people and explanations.

02:00.954 --> 02:06.927 align:left position:62.5%,start line:93.33% size:37.5%
And that issue had to be covered and was covered.

02:07.027 --> 02:11.498 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JOHN YANG: Even before the first meeting,
Uber chief executive Travis Kalanick quit

02:11.598 --> 02:13.066 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
the group over the issue.

02:13.166 --> 02:16.203 align:left position:62.5%,start line:93.33% size:37.5%
He had been pressed by both workers and customers.

02:16.303 --> 02:21.074 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
He wrote to employees: "We will continue to
advocate for just change on immigration, but

02:21.174 --> 02:24.144 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
staying on the council was going to get in
the way of that."

02:24.244 --> 02:29.750 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The same kind of pressure is driving a nationalboycott of Trump products.

02:29.850 --> 02:36.023 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Retailer Nordstrom is dropping Ivanka Trump'sfashion line, citing poor sales.

02:36.123 --> 02:39.126 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
Today brought the number of Mr. Trump's executive
actions to 20.

02:39.226 --> 02:44.564 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
DONALD TRUMP: Today, we're signing core principles
for regulating the United States financial

02:44.664 --> 02:45.599 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
system.

02:45.699 --> 02:47.467 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
Doesn't get much bigger than that, right?

02:47.567 --> 02:51.671 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JOHN YANG: That executive order directed the
Treasury Department to look for ways to roll

02:51.772 --> 02:54.975 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
back the Dodd-Frank Act's regulations.

02:55.075 --> 02:58.478 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The 2010 legislation was in response to the
financial crisis.

02:58.578 --> 03:02.416 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
It was intended rein in big banks and protect
consumers.

03:02.516 --> 03:07.421 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The president also signed a memorandum aimed
at blocking a retirement savings regulation

03:07.521 --> 03:10.257 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
called the fiduciary rule.

03:10.357 --> 03:14.895 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Set to take effect in April, it's aimed at
making brokers put clients' interests first

03:14.995 --> 03:17.931 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
when recommending investments for retirement
planning.

03:18.031 --> 03:22.669 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Administration officials call it a solution
in search of a problem, and the financial

03:22.769 --> 03:25.705 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
industry has strongly opposed it.

03:25.806 --> 03:30.343 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Republican Representative Ann Wagner of Missouri
championed efforts to stop the regulation.

03:30.444 --> 03:32.179 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:32.279 --> 03:36.149 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
ANN WAGNER (R), Missouri: Taking the boot
off the neck of the American people and this

03:36.249 --> 03:38.351 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
economy moving forward.

03:38.452 --> 03:40.220 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
People are crying out to cut the red tape.

03:40.320 --> 03:47.327 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
They are finished with the Washington knows
best, top-down bureaucratic regulation that

03:47.427 --> 03:50.263 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
is absolutely suffocating American families.

03:50.363 --> 03:55.001 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JOHN YANG: Mr. Trump capped the second week
of his presidency by heading to Florida for

03:55.102 --> 03:58.705 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
a weekend at his Mar-a-Lago resort.

03:58.805 --> 04:03.610 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
On his way back to the White House on Monday,
Mr. Trump will spend his first major event

04:03.710 --> 04:05.245 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
addressing troops.

04:05.345 --> 04:09.583 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
He will be at Central Command at MacDill AirForce Base on Tampa Bay -- Judy.

04:09.683 --> 04:13.720 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, John, a lot going on at
the White House this week, right up until

04:13.820 --> 04:15.589 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
today.

04:15.689 --> 04:19.226 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The president's senior adviser Kellyanne Conway
in a situation where she had to retract a

04:19.326 --> 04:20.994 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
statement she made in an interview yesterday.

04:21.094 --> 04:22.195 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: That's right.

04:22.295 --> 04:24.698 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
She talked to Chris Matthews on MSNBC last
night.

04:24.798 --> 04:29.903 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
She was defending the president's immigration
order and she said that the media never reported

04:30.003 --> 04:31.838 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
the Bowling Green massacre.

04:31.938 --> 04:36.042 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
Well, one of the reasons the media never reportedit is because it never happened.

04:36.143 --> 04:42.582 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Today, she acknowledged on Twitter that she
had confused it with the arrest of two Iraqi

04:42.682 --> 04:47.821 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
-- Iraqis who had been radicalized in Bowling
Green, Kentucky.

04:47.921 --> 04:52.492 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
She apologized, but she also complained aboutbeing criticized for her slip.

04:52.592 --> 04:54.327 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
&nbsp;
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, John, you mentioned Twitter.

04:54.427 --> 04:58.765 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The president has continued to be active on
Twitter, this morning tweeting again about

04:58.865 --> 05:04.437 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
that phone conversation that he had, reportedly
heated conversation, with the prime minister

05:04.538 --> 05:08.475 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
of Australia, and then another one about,
of all people, Arnold Schwarzenegger.

05:08.575 --> 05:09.476 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: That's right.

05:09.576 --> 05:11.311 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I will take them in order.

05:11.411 --> 05:16.683 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The prime minister of Australia said that
the phone call was candid and frank, which,

05:16.783 --> 05:20.620 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
of course, is diplomatic language often for
a shouting match.

05:20.720 --> 05:25.959 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
But he did say that, contrary to reports,
that Mr. Trump didn't hang up on him.

05:26.059 --> 05:31.031 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
So, Mr. Trump thanked him for straightening
that out and called the original reports fake

05:31.131 --> 05:32.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
news.

05:32.966 --> 05:36.336 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
And then on Arnold Schwarzenegger, there was
a little back and forth yesterday from the

05:36.436 --> 05:40.273 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Prayer Breakfast, when he talked about the
ratings.

05:40.373 --> 05:45.378 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Mr. Schwarzenegger replied that maybe they
wanted to switch jobs, that Mr. Trump was

05:45.478 --> 05:49.816 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
better at ratings and that he was -- Americans
could sleep at night.

05:49.916 --> 05:54.854 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
He said, yes, Arnold Schwarzenegger did a
really bad job as governor of California and

05:54.955 --> 05:58.124 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
even worse on "The Apprentice," but at least
he tried hard.

05:58.225 --> 06:01.161 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, it sounds like that settles
that.

06:01.261 --> 06:02.896 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

06:02.996 --> 06:07.400 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JUDY WOODRUFF: John Yang, after another busy
week at the White House, thank you.

06:07.500 --> 06:12.205 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
And in the day's other news: January's job
creation was the best since last September.

06:12.305 --> 06:17.711 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The Labor Department reports that U.S. employers
added 227,000 new jobs.

06:17.811 --> 06:21.047 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
The unemployment rate ticked up to 4.8 percent.

06:21.147 --> 06:24.985 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
Now, that is more Americans looking for work.

06:25.085 --> 06:28.822 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
President Trump welcomed the report and said
that it shows a -- quote -- "great spirit"

06:28.922 --> 06:30.657 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the country.

06:30.757 --> 06:34.461 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The jobs report and the president's move to
scale back financial regulations fueled a

06:34.561 --> 06:36.263 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
rally on Wall Street.

06:36.363 --> 06:41.868 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The Dow Jones industrial average gained 186
points to close back above 20000.

06:41.968 --> 06:46.573 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The Nasdaq rose 30, and the S&amp;P 500 added
16.

06:46.673 --> 06:53.013 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The Trump administration imposed new economic
sanctions today on 13 people and a dozen companies

06:53.113 --> 06:54.481 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in Iran.

06:54.581 --> 06:58.785 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
It is a response to Iran's test this month
of a ballistic missile.

06:58.885 --> 07:03.523 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Early this morning, the president tweeted:--
quote -- "Iran is playing with fire."

07:03.623 --> 07:08.862 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
And Press Secretary Sean Spicer said the president
isn't ruling out other responses, including

07:08.962 --> 07:10.664 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
military action.

07:10.764 --> 07:11.898 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press Secretary:
These sanctions today I think are going to

07:11.998 --> 07:15.835 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
be very, very strong and impactful.

07:15.935 --> 07:20.340 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
And I hope that Iran realizes that, after
the provocative measures that they have taken,

07:20.440 --> 07:24.044 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
that they understand that this president,
this administration is not going to sit back

07:24.144 --> 07:25.879 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and take it lightly.

07:25.979 --> 07:28.548 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Later in the day, when Mr.
Trump was asked about Iran, he said -- quote

07:28.648 --> 07:30.383 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
-- "They're not behaving."

07:30.483 --> 07:36.089 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
But Iran's foreign minister, Javad Zarif,
posted his own tweet, saying -- quote -- "Iran

07:36.189 --> 07:37.924 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
unmoved by threats.

07:38.024 --> 07:39.859 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Will never initiate war."

07:39.959 --> 07:45.332 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
We will get into the details of these sanctions,
and the implications, after the news summary.

07:45.432 --> 07:51.604 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
In Paris, security fears surged again today
when a man with a machete attacked guards

07:51.705 --> 07:54.207 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
outside the famed Louvre museum.

07:54.307 --> 07:59.646 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The attacker, said to be an Egyptian national,
shouted "God is great" in Arabic.

07:59.746 --> 08:04.417 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
He slightly injured one soldier before beingshot and wounded himself.

08:04.517 --> 08:08.088 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Museum-goers had to run away or shelter in
place.

08:08.188 --> 08:13.293 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
A senior Israeli official is welcoming a U.S.statement on settlements.

08:13.393 --> 08:19.399 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
In it, the Trump White House says they don't
impede peace, but that constructing new ones

08:19.499 --> 08:23.737 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
or expanding existing ones -- quote -- "may
not be helpful."

08:23.837 --> 08:29.275 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
In response, Israel's deputy foreign minister
said today: "The conclusion is that more building

08:29.376 --> 08:31.211 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is not the problem."

08:31.311 --> 08:36.583 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
A spokesman for Palestinian President Mahmoud
Abbas called for action to prevent settlement

08:36.683 --> 08:38.451 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
expansion.

08:38.551 --> 08:43.890 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
U.S. Defense Secretary James Mattis reassured
South Korea and Japan today that the U.S.

08:43.990 --> 08:46.059 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
is still committed to defending them.

08:46.159 --> 08:51.231 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
His first trip abroad followed candidate Trump's
complaints that the allies should do more

08:51.331 --> 08:53.099 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for their own defense.

08:53.199 --> 08:58.605 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
In Seoul, Mattis met with his South Korean
counterpart, and he underscored American support

08:58.705 --> 09:00.540 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to deter North Korea.

09:00.640 --> 09:03.676 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
JAMES MATTIS, U.S. Secretary of Defense: America's
commitments to defending our allies and to

09:03.777 --> 09:08.815 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
upholding our extended deterrence guarantees
remain ironclad.

09:08.915 --> 09:14.421 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Any attack on the United States or on our
allies will be defeated and any use of nuclear

09:14.521 --> 09:19.092 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
weapons would be met with a response that
would be effective and overwhelming.

09:19.192 --> 09:23.229 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Mattis later met with Japan's
prime minister in Tokyo.

09:23.329 --> 09:30.370 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The U.S. has more than 28,000 troops in SouthKorea and about 50,000 in Japan.

09:30.470 --> 09:36.409 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The U.N. human rights commissioner is accusing
security forces in Myanmar of mass killings

09:36.509 --> 09:39.846 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
and gang rapes against Rohingya Muslims.

09:39.946 --> 09:45.652 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
A report today charges that there's a campaign
to drive them out of the mostly Buddhist nation.

09:45.752 --> 09:51.124 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Myanmar has denied previous allegations of
abuses against its Muslim minority.

09:51.224 --> 09:54.394 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
It says it is battling insurgents.

09:54.494 --> 09:59.966 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Back in this country, a Justice Department
lawyer told a federal court today that 100,000

10:00.066 --> 10:04.571 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
entry visas have been revoked under PresidentTrump's immigration order.

10:04.671 --> 10:08.741 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The State Department said later that the numberis actually fewer than 60,000.

10:08.842 --> 10:15.081 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Meanwhile, federal judges in Boston, Seattle
and Virginia held hearings on legal challenges

10:15.181 --> 10:16.382 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to the order.

10:16.483 --> 10:19.252 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
So far, at this hour, there's been a split
in rulings.

10:19.352 --> 10:25.425 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The Boston judge declined to extend the partial
block on the Trump order, while, in Virginia,

10:25.525 --> 10:29.829 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
a judge allowed a lawsuit challenge to go
forward.

10:29.929 --> 10:33.633 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
The stage is set now for a Senate showdown
on Betsy DeVos.

10:33.733 --> 10:37.804 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
She is President Trump's nominee to be secretary
of education.

10:37.904 --> 10:43.610 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Senators voted early this morning to end debate,
with Democrats and Republicans senators jousting

10:43.710 --> 10:44.911 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
