42:01.052 --> 42:03.454 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
critics and civil rights activists.

42:03.554 --> 42:09.293 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
A new Oscar-nominated documentary opening
today explores his life and legacy.

42:09.394 --> 42:10.428 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Jeffrey Brown has our look.

42:10.528 --> 42:13.331 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
It's part of our series Beyond the Red Carpet.

42:13.431 --> 42:16.467 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
And a warning: It contains offensive language.

42:16.567 --> 42:24.809 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JAMES BALDWIN, Author/Civil Rights Activist:
There are days -- this is one of them -- when

42:24.909 --> 42:28.780 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
you wonder what your role is in this countryand what your future is in it.

42:28.880 --> 42:33.050 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: His words never really went
away, but the writer James Baldwin, speaking

42:33.151 --> 42:38.055 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
here on public television in 1963, feels as
relevant as ever.

42:38.156 --> 42:44.862 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JAMES BALDWIN: I'm terrified at the moral
apathy, the death of the heart, which is happening

42:44.962 --> 42:46.731 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in my country.

42:46.831 --> 42:53.471 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
These people have deluded themselves for so
long, that they really don't think I'm human.

42:53.571 --> 42:59.477 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
NARRATOR: "The story of the Negro in America
is the story of America.

42:59.577 --> 43:01.579 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
It is not a pretty story."

43:01.679 --> 43:06.451 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: The clip is from a new documentary
that draws a portrait of the artist, though

43:06.551 --> 43:11.522 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
not as a traditional film biography, and of
the fractured and racially divided world he

43:11.622 --> 43:13.224 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
shone a searing light on.

43:13.324 --> 43:16.861 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
NARRATOR: "I was free only in battle, but
never free to rest."

43:16.961 --> 43:18.963 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: It's called "I Am Not Your
Negro."

43:19.063 --> 43:22.900 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
RAOUL PECK, Director, "I Am Not Your Negro":
James Baldwin is probably, for me and for

43:23.000 --> 43:29.507 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
many other people, one of the most extraordinary
authors in this country, black or white.

43:29.607 --> 43:31.843 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
And he is somebody who changed my life.

43:31.943 --> 43:35.913 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: Director Raoul Peck is best
known for documentaries and dramas about the

43:36.013 --> 43:43.120 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Congolese leader Patrice Lumumba, and "Sometimes
in April" about the Rwandan genocide.

43:43.221 --> 43:47.925 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Born in Haiti and raised in the Congo, Peck
says that, for him, James Baldwin was an early

43:48.025 --> 43:52.163 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
and abiding influence about how to see and
encounter the world.

43:52.263 --> 44:00.605 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
RAOUL PECK: It gave, suddenly, an explanation
to feelings that I had towards racism, toward

44:00.705 --> 44:08.980 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
opportunities, toward politics and justice
and injustice, you know, a lot of things that,

44:09.080 --> 44:15.586 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
as a young man, that you have, but because
there are not so many authors where you feel

44:15.686 --> 44:19.557 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
you are represented, or the same on cinema.

44:19.657 --> 44:24.262 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
There were not so many films where you saw
your own narrative on the screen.

44:24.362 --> 44:25.863 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes, that voice.

44:25.963 --> 44:28.466 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
RAOUL PECK: That voice, and to feel you belong.

44:28.566 --> 44:34.038 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: Baldwin was born in Harlem
in 1924 and spent his youth there.

44:34.138 --> 44:38.042 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
He later lived for years in France, where
he felt he could live more freely as a black

44:38.142 --> 44:39.844 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
gay man.

44:39.944 --> 44:44.882 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
He became known for essays, such as "Notes
of a Native Son" and "The Fire Next Time,"

44:44.982 --> 44:50.488 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
novels including "Go Tell It on the Mountain"
and "Giovanni's Room," and much more, including

44:50.588 --> 44:53.691 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
his role as a public commentator, debater
and witness.

44:53.791 --> 44:59.063 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JAMES BALDWIN: Again, like most white Americans
I have now encountered, they have no -- I'm

44:59.163 --> 45:00.965 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
sure they nothing whatever against Negroes.

45:01.065 --> 45:02.800 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
That's really not the question.

45:02.900 --> 45:06.237 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
No, the question is really a kind of apathy
and ignorance, which is a price we pay for

45:06.337 --> 45:08.105 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
segregation.

45:08.205 --> 45:10.041 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
That's what segregation means, that you don't
know what's happening on the other side of

45:10.141 --> 45:11.943 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
the world because you don't want to know.

45:12.043 --> 45:17.648 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
NARRATOR: "I was in some way in those years,
without entirely realizing it, the great black

45:17.748 --> 45:19.784 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
hope of the great white father."

45:19.884 --> 45:25.156 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: The film uses Baldwin's own
words and writings read by Samuel L. Jackson,

45:25.256 --> 45:31.362 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
particularly a short manuscript he never completed
about three men he'd known, all of them assassinated

45:31.462 --> 45:37.835 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
before the age of 40, Malcolm X, Medgar Evers,
and Martin Luther King.

45:37.935 --> 45:42.540 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
As a film credit puts it, the film is, in
a sense, written by James Baldwin.

45:42.640 --> 45:50.615 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
RAOUL PECK: So, my job is to find the book,
and to recreate it, and which is then the

45:50.715 --> 45:52.416 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
film for me.

45:52.516 --> 45:57.622 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
That was, of course, the line and the storyline
that I needed to construct that film.

45:57.722 --> 45:59.190 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: That's interesting.

45:59.290 --> 46:02.360 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
So, to make the film that he set out to do,but wasn't able to finish.

46:02.460 --> 46:03.661 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
RAOUL PECK: Yes, exactly.

46:03.761 --> 46:05.229 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
&nbsp;
Exactly.

46:05.329 --> 46:08.966 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
So, that's why, as a filmmaker, I feel thatI was just the messenger.

46:09.066 --> 46:14.772 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I was just the person in charge to put it
together, but he already wrote it.

46:14.872 --> 46:21.545 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
That's why I was very proud to be able to
put "directed by Raoul Peck, but written by

46:21.646 --> 46:25.683 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
James Baldwin," because he wrote every single
word in the film.

46:25.783 --> 46:28.185 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I didn't add anything.

46:28.285 --> 46:30.755 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
I deconstructed, but I didn't -- wrote it.

46:30.855 --> 46:36.160 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JAMES BALDWIN: What black people have to do
is try to find out in their own hearts why

46:36.260 --> 46:39.530 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
it was necessary to have a nigger in the firstplace, because I'm not a nigger.

46:39.630 --> 46:40.765 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
&nbsp;
I'm a man.

46:40.865 --> 46:44.568 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
But if you think I'm a nigger, it means you
need it.

46:44.669 --> 46:49.473 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: In his film, though, Peck has
done what Baldwin, who died in 1987, could

46:49.573 --> 46:55.680 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
not: connect his time to ours through images
of Ferguson, Trayvon Martin, and more.

46:55.780 --> 47:02.753 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
RAOUL PECK: When I started 10 years ago to
work on this project, it was because I already

47:02.853 --> 47:05.222 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
felt that something was wrong.

47:05.322 --> 47:11.562 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
It was for us, you know, scary, because it
was actually something we were working on.

47:11.662 --> 47:15.032 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
And now we have visual of that, images.

47:15.132 --> 47:22.973 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
And it made the film more urgent for us, but
it didn't really change the origin or the

47:23.074 --> 47:29.480 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
needs for this movie and the need to go back
to Baldwin, because Baldwin gave us the fundamentals.

47:29.580 --> 47:32.516 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
NARRATOR: "Well, I am tired.

47:32.616 --> 47:34.885 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
I don't know how it will come about.

47:34.985 --> 47:40.691 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I know that, no matter how it comes about,
it will be bloody.

47:40.791 --> 47:42.493 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It will be hard.

47:42.593 --> 47:47.631 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I still believe that we can do with this country
something that has not been done before.

47:47.732 --> 47:52.970 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
We are misled here because we think of numbers.

47:53.070 --> 47:55.206 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You don't need numbers.

47:55.306 --> 47:56.874 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You need passion.

47:56.974 --> 47:59.910 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
And this is proven by the history of the world."

48:00.010 --> 48:06.717 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
RAOUL PECK: He was already a classic, and
he wrote those things 40, 50 years ago.

48:06.817 --> 48:12.823 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
And watching the film, you think that he would
have -- he wrote that in the morning, the

48:12.923 --> 48:17.928 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
morning before watching the film, becausethose words are so accurate.

48:18.028 --> 48:20.464 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
They are so prescient, you know?

48:20.564 --> 48:24.468 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
&nbsp;
And so it back-fold, that you can do it better.

48:24.568 --> 48:28.939 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JEFFREY BROWN: "I Am Not Your Negro" will
compete in the best documentary category at

48:29.039 --> 48:31.942 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
the Academy Awards on February 26.

48:32.042 --> 48:40.217 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
From Washington, I'm Jeffrey Brown for the
"PBS NewsHour."

48:40.317 --> 48:51.128 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Mansoor Shams served in the
United States Marine Corps from 2000 to 2004.

48:51.228 --> 48:56.600 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Recently, he has been traveling around the
country with a simple sign that reads: "I'm

48:56.700 --> 48:59.236 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
a Muslim and a U.S. Marine.

48:59.336 --> 49:01.071 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Ask anything."

49:01.172 --> 49:04.408 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
"NewsHour" producer Mike Fritz joined him
while he was on the streets of Baltimore to

49:04.508 --> 49:06.744 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
listen in to some of the conversations he
was having.

49:06.844 --> 49:09.346 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MANSOOR SHAMS, Former U.S. Marine: Do you
know that I have to believe in Jesus Christ

49:09.446 --> 49:10.881 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in order to be a Muslim?

49:10.981 --> 49:12.316 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
He's a very special person to us.

49:12.416 --> 49:13.317 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: Oh, yes.

49:13.417 --> 49:14.451 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
But he's more than a prophet.

49:14.552 --> 49:15.853 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MANSOOR SHAMS: But that's OK.

49:15.953 --> 49:17.021 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's where we differ.

49:17.121 --> 49:18.923 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
My name is Mansoor Shams.

49:19.023 --> 49:21.559 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm a former U.S. Marine.

49:21.659 --> 49:24.862 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I was born in Pakistan, came to the United
States at age 6.

49:24.962 --> 49:26.230 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm now 34 years old.

49:26.330 --> 49:30.301 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MAN: So, how are you Muslim and a Marine if
they hate you?

49:30.401 --> 49:32.469 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
MANSOOR SHAMS: Because that's what I am.

49:32.570 --> 49:34.004 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
MAN: It doesn't make sense.

49:34.104 --> 49:36.440 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
MANSOOR SHAMS: How did I start this project?

49:36.540 --> 49:40.511 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Well, it's interesting, because never would
I have thought that we would reach a state

49:40.611 --> 49:47.251 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
in our nation where we would be troubled or
confused or frustrated or divisive when it

49:47.351 --> 49:49.854 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
came to people who followed my faith.

49:49.954 --> 49:52.089 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
The more conversations that we have, the better.

49:52.189 --> 49:57.228 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Recently, I got to visit the cities of Houston,Denver, Portland, and Seattle.

49:57.328 --> 50:03.367 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
It's always a new experience in general, because
you don't know how people are going to react,

50:03.467 --> 50:07.438 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
and how they are going to take it.

50:07.538 --> 50:12.142 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MAN: ISIS, I thought they just chopped the
heads off.

50:12.243 --> 50:13.143 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
They don't chop your head off.

50:13.244 --> 50:14.144 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
They even have little children.

50:14.245 --> 50:15.179 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I couldn't even...

50:15.279 --> 50:16.146 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
MANSOOR SHAMS: They're horrendous people.

50:16.247 --> 50:17.615 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I agree with you.

50:17.715 --> 50:19.250 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
If ISIS caught me, they would put me -- break
me up into pieces.

50:19.350 --> 50:22.953 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Some of the questions that I get as I'm outand about relate to Sharia law.

50:23.053 --> 50:24.822 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
&nbsp;
That's a very big one.

50:24.922 --> 50:27.524 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
So, they will say, do you believe in Sharia
law as a United States Marine, as a Muslim?

50:27.625 --> 50:30.194 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
Of course, my answer is, yes, I do.

50:30.294 --> 50:31.962 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
But it's not the way that you believe in it.

50:32.062 --> 50:33.364 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
It's the way I believe in it.

50:33.464 --> 50:36.333 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I tell them that it's literally a path to
life-giving water.

50:36.433 --> 50:37.334 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a moral code.

50:37.434 --> 50:39.236 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
It tells me not to commit adultery.

50:39.336 --> 50:40.271 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
It tells me not to fornicate.

50:40.371 --> 50:42.673 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
It tells me not to drink, not to gamble.

50:42.773 --> 50:44.575 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
This is all forms of Sharia law.

50:44.675 --> 50:49.213 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
A lot of people are scared of perhaps people
who follow my belief system or even look like...

50:49.313 --> 50:50.214 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MAN: I love Muslims.

50:50.314 --> 50:51.215 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I love everybody, brother.

50:51.315 --> 50:52.216 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I love you.

50:52.316 --> 50:53.217 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MANSOOR SHAMS: Hey, man.

50:53.317 --> 50:54.218 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thanks, man.

50:54.318 --> 50:55.219 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You motivate me, man.

50:55.319 --> 50:56.553 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

50:56.654 --> 50:57.755 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
MANSOOR SHAMS: I think Americans do not understand
Islam.

50:57.855 --> 51:00.157 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
It's been among -- amongst America for 200
years.

51:00.257 --> 51:01.959 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's always been there.

51:02.059 --> 51:03.260 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MAN: And, see, that's what he's trying to
protect us from is the radical Muslim, the

51:03.360 --> 51:11.001 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
ones that are intending to come over here
and kill us.

51:11.101 --> 51:17.074 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MANSOOR SHAMS: In the larger scheme of things,
when you paint an entire religion or an entire

51:17.174 --> 51:20.778 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
nation, for that matter, with a broad brush,
and anyone who is an immigrant who's come

51:20.878 --> 51:25.049 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
to this country, ask them how hard it is to
come to this country.

51:25.149 --> 51:26.517 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
OK?

51:26.617 --> 51:28.352 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
My feelings of Donald Trump, or President
Trump, has been mixed.

51:28.452 --> 51:34.124 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
It's helped me to see another America thatI thought we had gone far past.

51:34.224 --> 51:39.163 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
However, I did take the time to write him
a letter and to say that he could use me as

51:39.263 --> 51:40.197 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a potential resource.

51:40.297 --> 51:43.133 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
I don't know if he's received it.

51:43.233 --> 51:44.234 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
It wasn't a partisan letter.

51:44.335 --> 51:46.437 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
It wasn't a negative letter.

51:46.537 --> 51:51.442 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
